column_description: A unique identifier for each television channel, represented as an integer
The name of the television channel, represented as text (e.g., BBC One, ITV)
value_description: BBC One, ITV, BBC Two, Channel 4, Channel 5

column_description: The channel number on analogue terrestrial television, represented as text (e.g., '1' for BBC One). If unavailable, it is marked as 'unavailable'
The channel number on digital terrestrial television, represented as text (e.g., 'HD' or '2'). If unavailable, it is marked as 'unavailable'
The website or online platform where the channel can be accessed, represented as text (e.g., 'bbc.co.uk'). If unavailable, it is marked as 'unavailable'
value_description: bbc.co.uk, ITV - itv.com, channel4.com, unavailable, itv.com
